The paper discusses the computational complexity of the Tetravex game, which involves tiling a square grid with labeled tiles. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions generating Tetravex problems and observing phase transition behavior, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational geometry (cs.CG), and game theory (cs.GT).
